The goal is to prove `map_id` for the `Comma_category_dom` functor.
The functor $P: (d \downarrow E) \to D$ projects an object $(d, e, f)$ to $d$ and a morphism $(h, k)$ to $h$.
The identity morphism in the comma category on an object $X = (d, e, f)$ is given by $(\text{id}_d, \text{id}_e)$.
We need to show $P(\text{id}_X) = \text{id}_{P(X)}$.
LHS: $P(\text{id}_X) = P(\text{id}_{(d,e,f)}) = P((\text{id}_d, \text{id}_e)) = \text{id}_d$.
RHS: $\text{id}_{P(X)} = \text{id}_{P((d,e,f))} = \text{id}_d$.
The equality holds definitionally, but since the definitions of `id` and `F` involve pattern matching on the object $X$, we must destruct $X$ to allow reduction.

```lean
